  "body": "The following example outputs the correct HTML:\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nimport * as React from \"react\"\r\nimport {renderToString} from 'react-dom/server'\r\n\r\nconst B: any = () => <div>b</div>;\r\nconsole.log(renderToString(<div><B /></div>));\r\n// <div data-reactroot=\"\"><div>b</div></div>\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever, output is escaped when using es6 class:\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nimport * as React from \"react\"\r\nimport {renderToString} from 'react-dom/server'\r\n\r\nclass B extends React.Component {\r\n  public render() {\r\n    return \"<div>b</div>\"\r\n  }\r\n}\r\nconsole.log(renderToString(<div><B /></div>));\r\n// <div data-reactroot=\"\">&lt;div&gt;b&lt;/div&gt;</div>\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nIs there any solution?\r\n\r\n--------------------------------\r\n\r\nReact version: 16.8.6\r\nReact-Dom version: 16.8.6\r\nTypescript version: 3.4.5",
